steep,g_auto/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F537aedb2-fc93-44d6-9c95-d81e1cc7ceb5_1372x780.png\"><img class=\"img-OACg1c smSquare-NGbPBa pencraft pc-reset\" src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!D6T1!,w_140,h_140,c_fill,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep,g_auto/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F537aedb2-fc93-44d6-9c95-d81e1cc7ceb5_1372x780.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" alt=\"The New Caesars Podcast\" width=\"140\" height=\"140\" style=\"text-decoration: unset;list-style: none;border: none !important;vertical-align: middle;display: block;-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic;max-width: 100%;margin: 0 auto;height: 70px!important;object-fit: cover;width: 70px;\"></picture></a></div></td><td width=\"16\" style=\"min-width:16px;\"></td><td style=\"vertical-align:middle;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"auto\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td><h4 class=\"pencraft pc-reset color-pub-primary-text-NyXPlw line-height-24-jnGwiv font-display-nhmvtD size-20-P_cSRT weight-bold-DmI9lw reset-IxiVJZ\" style=\"list-style: none;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;-moz-osx-font-smoothing: antialiased;-webkit-appearance: optimizelegibility;-moz-appearance: optimizelegibility;appearance: optimizelegibility;font-family: 'SF Pro Display',-apple-system-headline,system-ui,-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif,'Apple Color Emoji','Segoe UI Emoji','Segoe UI Symbol';font-weight: 700;margin: 0;color: #363737;line-height: 24px;font-size: 20px;text-decoration: unset;\"><a href=\"https://substack.com/redirect/2930430e-54e5-40ce-bc12-a28c3bc373ec?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8\" style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);text-decoration: none;\">The New Caesars Podcast</a></h4></td></tr><tr><td><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"auto\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"vertical-align:middle;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"auto\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"vertical-align:middle;\"><div class=\"pencraft pc-reset color-pub-secondary-text-hGQ02T line-height-20-t4M0El font-meta-MWBumP size-11-NuY2Zx weight-medium-fw81nC transform-uppercase-yKDgcq reset-IxiVJZ meta-EgzBVA\" style=\"list-style: none;font-size: 11px;line-height: 20px;text-decoration: unset;color: #777777;margin: 0;font-family: 'SF Compact',-apple-system,system-ui,-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif,'Apple Color Emoji','Segoe UI Emoji','Segoe UI Symbol';font-weight: 500;text-transform: uppercase;letter-spacing: .2px;\"><a class=\"inheritColor-WetTGJ\" href=\"https://substack.com/profile/2769871-claire-berlinski\" style=\"color: inherit;text-decoration: none;\">Claire Berlinski</a></div></td><td width=\"4\" style=\"min-width:4px;\"></td><td style=\"vertical-align:middle;\"><div class=\"pencraft pc-reset color-pub-secondary-text-hGQ02T reset-IxiVJZ\" style=\"list-style: none;font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;text-decoration: unset;color: #777777;margin: 0;\">&#183;</div></td></tr></tbody></table></td><td width=\"4\" style=\"min-width:4px;\"></td><td style=\"vertical-align:middle;\"><div class=\"pencraft pc-reset color-pub-secondary-text-hGQ02T line-height-20-t4M0El font-meta-MWBumP size-11-NuY2Zx weight-medium-fw81nC transform-uppercase-yKDgcq reset-IxiVJZ meta-EgzBVA\" style=\"list-style: none;font-size: 11px;line-height: 20px;text-decoration: unset;color: #777777;margin: 0;font-family: 'SF Compact',-apple-system,system-ui,-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif,'Apple Color Emoji','Segoe UI Emoji','Segoe UI Symbol';font-weight: 500;text-transform: uppercase;letter-spacing: .2px;\">October 17, 2022</div></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"auto\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" style=\"padding-top:0px;padding-bottom:0px;\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"vertical-align:middle;\"><a class=\"pencraft pc-reset align-center-y7ZD4w line-height-20-t4M0El font-text-qe4AeH size-13-hZTUKr weight-medium-fw81nC reset-IxiVJZ\" href=\"https://substack.com/redirect/2930430e-54e5-40ce-bc12-a28c3bc373ec?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8\" style=\"list-style: none;color: unset;text-align: center;text-decoration: unset;margin: 0;font-size: 13px;line-height: 20px;font-family: system-ui,-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif,'Apple Color Emoji','Segoe UI Emoji','Segoe UI Symbol';font-weight: 500;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"auto\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"vertical-align:middle;\"><span class=\"pencraft pc-reset color-accent-BVX_7M line-height-20-t4M0El font-text-qe4AeH size-14-MLPa7j weight-regular-mUq6Gb reset-IxiVJZ link-HREYZo\" style=\"list-style: none;text-decoration: unset;color: rgb(255,103,25);margin: 0;font-size: 14px;line-height: 20px;font-family: system-ui,-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif,'Apple Color Emoji','Segoe UI Emoji','Segoe UI Symbol';font-weight: 400;\">Read full story</span></td></tr></tbody></table></a></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></div><div style=\"font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;\"><hr style=\"margin: 32px 0;padding: 0;height: 1px;background: rgb(0,0,0,.1);border: none;\"></div><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\"><span>As for your question, I don&#8217;t think it makes sense</span><strong> </strong><span>to grade the world by headline-events alone. You&#8217;ve done something intelligent by sorting events into authoritarian persistence, democratic rebound, and ambiguous cases, but you&#8217;re counting &#8220;autocrat fell&#8221; as &#8220;democracy improved,&#8221; and they aren&#8217;t the same thing. The fall of a tyrant may be an opening, but it isn&#8217;t institutions&#8212;not yet, anyway.</span></p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\"><span>Globally, liberal democracy remains in its long recession. (I use the term &#8220;recession&#8221; because this is the term favored by political scientists and the media, but I dislike it, because it suggests that this is a phenomenon similar to an economic recession: cyclical, and highly likely to abate with time. Perhaps. But we don&#8217;t know yet.)  The world as a whole still looks grim. Freedom House records the twentieth consecutive year of decline in global freedom, and V-Dem&#8217;s 2026 report&#8212;which Dan and I discussed on </span><strong><a href=\"https://substack.com/redirect/3679aedd-c403-47eb-8a78-635fb092cf5c?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8\" style=\"color: #e11d48;text-decoration: none;\">a recent episode of Critical Conditions</a></strong><span>&#8212;reports that only 18 countries, about 10 percent of the nations of the world, are  democratizing. Nearly a quarter are autocratizing.</span></p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">The picture isn&#8217;t flat-out catastrophic. The EIU&#8217;s 2025 Democracy Index is more cautiously positive. After eight years of decline, their democracy scores stabilized in 2025. So the story may be changing from uniform democratic retreat to violent sorting: Some systems are hardening into autocracy; others are developing antibodies. </p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\"><span>The world looks pretty grim, in the aggregate. It looks more polarized. Autocracies are more openly autocratic, democracies are more anxious, and some societies </span><em>may</em><span> be showing that democratic erosion is reversible.</span></p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">I think your list is too positive, but only because you treat every authoritarian setback as a democratic gain. I would distinguish sharply between &#8220;weakened autocrat&#8221; and &#8220;strengthened democracy.&#8221; Assad&#8217;s fall, for example, is unquestionably good if the comparison is with Assad. But Syria&#8217;s post-Assad condition is not democratic. It has improved from a catastrophically low base, but the institutional questions remain unresolved. </p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">Even more so for Iran. Khamenei&#8217;s death and the regime&#8217;s evident crisis are hardly the same as the fall of the Islamic Republic. The regime continues to repress brutally; it is on an unbearable execution spree&#8212;I can hardly bear to look at the faces of the young, beautiful people it is executing every day. Nothing, so far, suggests it&#8217;s experiencing a democratic transition. </p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">So the category you want here is &#8220;authoritarian rupture,&#8221; not democratic consolidation. Hopeful openings don&#8217;t count as victories for liberal democracy until power is actually constrained, succession is regularized, coercive institutions are subordinated, and the opposition can organize without being murdered. The fall of an autocrat is the end of an era, not the beginning of a constitution.</p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">But you&#8217;re right to note the bright spots. Hungary really matters. Orb&#225;n&#8217;s defeat is a major case because it shows that electoral-authoritarian systems, even paradigmatic ones, can still be beaten electorally; what&#8217;s more, the new government has a clear mandate to restore the rule of law. So I&#8217;m optimistic with you,, but let&#8217;s see where Hungary is a year from now. </p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\"><span>Yes, Taiwan and Canada belong in the positive column, but let&#8217;s not exaggerate. The 2024 election showed that Taiwan&#8217;s democracy is resilient even under intense pressure from Beijing. But that&#8217;s what we&#8217;d expect to see, isn&#8217;t it? It&#8217;s a sign of how far our standards have fallen that we get excited when a mature, long-consolidated democracy holds a peaceful, free, and fair election. The same is true of Canada&#8217;s election. Canada isn&#8217;t an autocracy in need of rescue. We </span><em>expect</em><span> to see free and fair elections in Canada. So I&#8217;m glad that Taiwan and Canada are still capable of transferring power peacefully, but the fact of it doesn&#8217;t mean liberal democracy is winning, it just means the fire hasn&#8217;t consumed </span><em>every</em><span> country on the planet, thank God.</span></p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">Brazil should be in the &#8220;cautiously positive&#8221; column. Bolsonaro&#8217;s conviction is a very significant example. We can only admire it. His effort to stage a coup wasn&#8217;t just inspired by January 6, it was organized by the same people. (I wrote about this here, and I wish it had attracted more attention, because the story is outrageous.) </p><div class=\"digestPostEmbed-flwiST custom-css-email-digest-post-embed\" data-component-name=\"DigestPostEmbedStatic\" style=\"margin-bottom: 20px;padding: 0;position: relative;font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"auto\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"https://substack.com/redirect/885ee15f-8a5b-4070-8501-2650952d3799?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8\" style=\"text-decoration: none;\"><h2 class=\"pencraft pc-reset color-pub-primary-text-NyXPlw line-height-36-XIK16z font-display-nhmvtD size-30-tZAWf_ weight-bold-DmI9lw reset-IxiVJZ\" style=\"list-style: none;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;-moz-osx-font-smoothing: antialiased;-webkit-appearance: optimizelegibility;-moz-appearance: optimizelegibility;appearance: optimizelegibility;font-family: 'SF Pro Display',-apple-system-headline,system-ui,-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif,'Apple Color Emoji','Segoe UI Emoji','Segoe UI Symbol';font-weight: 700;margin: 0;color: #363737;line-height: 36px;font-size: 30px;text-decoration: unset;\">Our Cretins </h2></a></td></tr><tr><td><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"auto\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"vertical-align:middle;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"auto\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"vertical-align:middle;\"><div class=\"pencraft pc-reset color-pub-secondary-text-hGQ02T line-height-20-t4M0El font-meta-MWBumP size-11-NuY2Zx weight-medium-fw81nC transform-uppercase-yKDgcq reset-IxiVJZ meta-EgzBVA\" style=\"list-style: none;font-size: 11px;line-height: 20px;text-decoration: unset;color: #777777;margin: 0;font-family: 'SF Compact',-apple-system,system-ui,-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif,'Apple Color Emoji','Segoe UI Emoji','Segoe UI Symbol';font-weight: 500;text-transform: uppercase;letter-spacing: .2px;\"><a class=\"inheritColor-WetTGJ\" href=\"https://substack.com/profile/2769871-claire-berlinski\" style=\"color: inherit;text-decoration: none;\">Claire Berlinski</a></div></td><td width=\"4\" style=\"min-width:4px;\"></td><td style=\"vertical-align:middle;\"><div class=\"pencraft pc-reset color-pub-secondary-text-hGQ02T reset-IxiVJZ\" style=\"list-style: none;font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;text-decoration: unset;color: #777777;margin: 0;\">&#183;</div></td></tr></tbody></table></td><td width=\"4\" style=\"min-width:4px;\"></td><td style=\"vertical-align:middle;\"><div class=\"pencraft pc-reset color-pub-secondary-text-hGQ02T line-height-20-t4M0El font-meta-MWBumP size-11-NuY2Zx weight-medium-fw81nC transform-uppercase-yKDgcq reset-IxiVJZ meta-EgzBVA\" style=\"list-style: none;font-size: 11px;line-height: 20px;text-decoration: unset;color: #777777;margin: 0;font-family: 'SF Compact',-apple-system,system-ui,-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif,'Apple Color Emoji','Segoe UI Emoji','Segoe UI Symbol';font-weight: 500;text-transform: uppercase;letter-spacing: .2px;\">January 13, 2023</div></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td><div class=\"pencraft pc-paddingTop-24 pc-reset\" style=\"text-decoration: unset;list-style: none;padding-top: 24px;font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;\"><a href=\"https://substack.com/redirect/885ee15f-8a5b-4070-8501-2650952d3799?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8\" style=\"text-decoration: none;\"><picture><source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!e9ok!,w_424,h_212,c_fill,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep,g_auto/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2722d1e5-197d-40f0-95c3-a15f1931a2c9_1140x528.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!e9ok!,w_848,h_424,c_fill,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep,g_auto/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2722d1e5-197d-40f0-95c3-a15f1931a2c9_1140x528.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!e9ok!,w_1272,h_636,c_fill,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep,g_auto/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2722d1e5-197d-40f0-95c3-a15f1931a2c9_1140x528.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!e9ok!,w_1300,h_650,c_fill,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep,g_auto/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2722d1e5-197d-40f0-95c3-a15f1931a2c9_1140x528.png 1300w\" sizes=\"100vw\"><img class=\"img-OACg1c fullWidth-Ta6aEE pencraft pc-reset\" src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!e9ok!,w_1300,h_650,c_fill,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep,g_auto/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2722d1e5-197d-40f0-95c3-a15f1931a2c9_1140x528.png\" sizes=\"100vw\" alt=\"Our Cretins \" srcset=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!e9ok!,w_424,h_212,c_fill,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep,g_auto/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2722d1e5-197d-40f0-95c3-a15f1931a2c9_1140x528.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!e9ok!,w_848,h_424,c_fill,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep,g_auto/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2722d1e5-197d-40f0-95c3-a15f1931a2c9_1140x528.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!e9ok!,w_1272,h_636,c_fill,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep,g_auto/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2722d1e5-197d-40f0-95c3-a15f1931a2c9_1140x528.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!e9ok!,w_1300,h_650,c_fill,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep,g_auto/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2722d1e5-197d-40f0-95c3-a15f1931a2c9_1140x528.png 1300w\" width=\"1300\" height=\"650\" style=\"text-decoration: unset;list-style: none;border: none !important;vertical-align: middle;display: block;-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic;max-width: 100%;height: auto;margin: 0 auto;object-fit: cover;width: 100%;max-height: 325px!important;\"></picture></a></div></td></tr><tr><td><a href=\"https://substack.com/redirect/885ee15f-8a5b-4070-8501-2650952d3799?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8\" style=\"text-decoration: none;\"><p class=\"pencraft pc-reset\" style=\"text-decoration: unset;list-style: none;margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\"></p><p class=\"caption-QiPycG\" style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">What happened on January 8 in Bras&#237;lia closely resembled what happened on January 6 two years before in the US Capitol. This is not a coincidence. The same circle of Americans&#8212;Steve Bannon, in particular&#8212;was intimately involved in the planning and incitement of the insurrection in Bras&#237;lia. If you were in any doubt that Trump and Bannon intended to foment the violence we saw at the Capitol on January 6, you now have your answer. They intended it. Bannon was so undeterred by our response that he tried it again.</p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\"></p></a></td></tr><tr><td><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"auto\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" style=\"padding-top:0px;padding-bottom:0px;\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"vertical-align:middle;\"><a class=\"pencraft pc-reset align-center-y7ZD4w line-height-20-t4M0El font-text-qe4AeH size-13-hZTUKr weight-medium-fw81nC reset-IxiVJZ\" href=\"https://substack.com/redirect/885ee15f-8a5b-4070-8501-2650952d3799?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8\" style=\"list-style: none;color: unset;text-align: center;text-decoration: unset;margin: 0;font-size: 13px;line-height: 20px;font-family: system-ui,-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif,'Apple Color Emoji','Segoe UI Emoji','Segoe UI Symbol';font-weight: 500;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"auto\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"vertical-align:middle;\"><span class=\"pencraft pc-reset color-accent-BVX_7M line-height-20-t4M0El font-text-qe4AeH size-14-MLPa7j weight-regular-mUq6Gb reset-IxiVJZ link-HREYZo\" style=\"list-style: none;text-decoration: unset;color: rgb(255,103,25);margin: 0;font-size: 14px;line-height: 20px;font-family: system-ui,-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif,'Apple Color Emoji','Segoe UI Emoji','Segoe UI Symbol';font-weight: 400;\">Read full story</span></td></tr></tbody></table></a></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></div><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">But I qualify my enthusiasm with the word &#8220;cautious&#8221; because Brazil&#8217;s democracy required the courts to defend it. Judicial defense of democracy is absolutely necessary in emergencies, but democracies can&#8217;t live forever on judicial heroics. Eventually, political parties and voters have to do the work. </p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\"><span>The Latin American cases you wonder about are why it&#8217;s probably best to avoid easy categorizations. Bukele represents a paradigmatic order-versus-liberty problem. The collapse of the homicide rate in El Salvador is real (although some claim, plausibly to my ear, that the figures are exaggerated). So is the mass detention architecture and the prolonged state of exception. No one should celebrate the latter. But no one celebrated El Salvador&#8217;s homicide rate, either. I don&#8217;t see this as a standard case: I find it perfectly natural that people ceased to care about the niceties of due process and the rule of law when the state was failing so spectacularly at a states&#8217;s foremost responsibility&#8212;providing security. I&#8217;ve never fully understood why El Salvador became so violent, but if your homicide rate is 106.3 per 100,000 people, you can expect people to become mighty authoritarian.</span><span class=\"footnote-anchor-email\" data-component-name=\"FootnoteAnchorToDOMStatic\" style=\"font-size: 20px;\">&#8310;</span></p><div class=\"captioned-image-container-static\" style=\"font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;margin: 32px auto;\"><figure style=\"width: 100%;margin: 0 auto;\"><table class=\"image-wrapper\" width=\"100%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOMStatic\" style=\"mso-padding-alt: 1em 0 1.6em;\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"text-align: center;\"></td><td class=\"content\" align=\"left\" width=\"1456\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><a class=\"image-link\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substack.com/redirect/eb642201-aa89-4e24-a3d3-d7c668aad49d?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8\" style=\"position: relative;flex-direction: column;align-items: center;padding: 0;width: auto;height: auto;border: none;text-decoration: none;display: block;margin: 0;\"><img class=\"wide-image\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/490c16e5-7da5-469c-a259-6007ecf4e58f_1926x942.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:712,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:504613,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://claireberlinski.substack.com/i/195512420?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F490c16e5-7da5-469c-a259-6007ecf4e58f_1926x942.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"268.95604395604397\" src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!00OA!,w_1100,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F490c16e5-7da5-469c-a259-6007ecf4e58f_1926x942.png\" style=\"border: none !important;vertical-align: middle;display: block;-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic;height: auto;margin-bottom: 0;width: auto !important;max-width: 100% !important;margin: 0 auto;\"></a></td><td style=\"text-align: center;\"></td></tr></tbody></table></figure></div><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">Milei is different. Argentina is a competitive democracy. Freedom House gives it good scores for a lively media, civil society, and public debate. (V-Dem&#8217;s 2026 report is concerned: It claims there have been attacks on freedom of expression, media freedom, and civil society.) I have to confess that my knowledge of Argentina is very superficial, so I would ask an Argentine what&#8217;s going on down there. </p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">Overall, the world is doing worse than I&#8217;d hoped, and better than I feared, but the United States is doing so badly that I can&#8217;t feel much optimism. Some countries matter more than others. Unless we end our authoritarian experiment and do so decisively, I fear that liberal democracy has no long-term hope anywhere. We&#8217;ve gone from being the guarantor of the liberal order to a state sponsor of democratic erosion, and a very powerful one. There&#8217;s a limit to how long the world&#8217;s liberal democracies can hold out when the most powerful countries in the world are working, simultaneously, to undermine them. You don&#8217;t need to accept V-Dem&#8217;s index numbers as inerrant to see the strategic implications of the US becoming an autocratizing basket case. The world&#8217;s liberal-democratic ecosystem has lost its greatest exemplar and its stabilizer. </p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">More bad news: The autocrats have learned. They rarely abolish elections outright. They degrade the media, intimidate civil society, capture courts, politicize statistics, corrupt procurement, weaponize migration, and turn democratic procedure into scenery. </p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">The good news is that societies have learned too. Voters can recognize the script earlier; courts sometimes hold; civil society preserves memories; and international pressure can matter.</p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">So my assessment isn&#8217;t &#8220;we&#8217;re winning&#8221; or &#8220;we&#8217;re doomed.&#8221; It&#8217;s that the age of the New Caesars has entered a more dangerous but more interesting phase. Caesarism is no longer advancing everywhere unopposed. It&#8217;s meeting resistance. But resistance isn&#8217;t the same as victory, and victory isn&#8217;t the same as reconstruction. The biggest question now is whether anti-authoritarian coalitions can move from saying &#8220;no&#8221; to building institutions that make the next Caesar harder to produce. </p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">The Caesars are no longer marching unimpeded. Some have stumbled; a few have fallen. But the factory that produces them is still open.</p><div style=\"font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;\"><hr style=\"margin: 32px 0;padding: 0;height: 1px;background: rgb(0,0,0,.1);border: none;\"></div><h3 class=\"header-anchor-post\" style=\"position: relative;font-family: 'SF Pro Display',-apple-system-headline,system-ui,-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif,'Apple Color Emoji','Segoe UI Emoji','Segoe UI Symbol';font-weight: bold;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;-moz-osx-font-smoothing: antialiased;-webkit-appearance: optimizelegibility;-moz-appearance: optimizelegibility;appearance: optimizelegibility;margin: 1em 0 0.625em 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 1.16em;font-size: 1.375em;text-align: center\"><strong>&#9739;&#9884;&#65039;&#127759;&#9884;&#65039;&#9739;&#9884;&#65039;&#127757;&#9884;&#65039;&#9739;&#9884;&#65039;&#127758;&#9884;&#65039;&#9739;</strong></h3><div style=\"font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;\"><hr style=\"margin: 32px 0;padding: 0;height: 1px;background: rgb(0,0,0,.1);border: none;\"></div><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\"><strong>QUESTION: The physical bases of </strong><em><strong>le Universe</strong></em><strong> seem wavy and cyclic. Is political/economic history also? If so, is not evolution incompatibly linear (progressive) in comparison, particularly as it achieves AI liftoff? Does evolution not, in its apex phase, attack&#8212;perhaps destroy&#8212;the helix of history itself?</strong></p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\"><strong>[I&#8217;m] suggesting that the progression of technology under the barbaric banner of biological (compete till death) evolution, gets back to the balances of Eden (virtually impossible) or&#8212;likely&#8212;carries on till earth is either desert or fields of glass; hence ending &#8220;historic&#8221; cycles. You must have some sort of cycles theory underpinning your </strong><em><strong>Weltanschauung</strong></em><strong>. The question is how resilient you believe cyclic permanence to be in the face of the dire threat of the acceleratingly apex animal.</strong></p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;text-align: right\"><em><span>&#8212;</span><strong>Paul Janos</strong></em></p><div style=\"font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;\"><hr style=\"margin: 32px 0;padding: 0;height: 1px;background: rgb(0,0,0,.1);border: none;\"></div><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\"><span>Hi Paul!</span><span class=\"footnote-anchor-email\" data-component-name=\"FootnoteAnchorToDOMStatic\" style=\"font-size: 20px;\">&#8311;</span><span> </span></p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">I think you&#8217;re asking whether political history is cyclical, whether technological evolution is linear, and whether AI breaks the old cycle by giving cyclical human beings irreversible powers. Is that right? If so, my answer is: yes, that is one of the central dangers. Human passions recur; technology accumulates. We keep replaying old dramas with more powerful tools.</p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">I don&#8217;t ascribe to a simple cyclical theory of history, though I understand the attraction of one. Political history plainly has recurring forms: oligarchy, demagogy, imperial overstretch, revolution, decadence, reform, restoration, war, exhaustion, renewal. Everything&#8217;s a footnote to Plato.</p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">But technology isn't cyclical in the same way, because it accumulates. Human beings stay recognizably human, but the instruments available to human folly become more powerful. That&#8217;s why I would never say history is a circle. It&#8217;s closer, as you point out, to a helix: recurring human patterns under conditions of increasing technical capacity. </p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">Politics is cyclical because human passions are recurrent; technology is cumulative because knowledge compounds. The crisis of modernity (an inherently pretentious phrase, but what can I do, that&#8217;s what it is) is the collision between those two facts. We keep reenacting ancient dramas&#8212;fear, pride, rivalry, resentment, utopianism, greed&#8212;but with instruments of ever-increasing power. So I think your premise is partly right. The same patterns recur, but at higher energy levels, so to speak. </p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">AI matters because it may raise the energy level so dramatically that the old mechanisms of correction&#8212;defeat, embarrassment, bankruptcy, institutional reform&#8212;come too late. Institutions evolved for human-speed politics may be overwhelmed by machine-speed finance, propaganda, warfare, surveillance, and scientific discovery. If the old cycle was ambition, overreach, collapse, recovery, the new danger is unrecoverable overreach.</p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\"><span>So I take your question </span><em>very</em><span> seriously. It&#8217;s at the center of most of what I write about these days. We may have finally built tools powerful enough to destroy the ecological and political conditions under which, previously, civilization renewed itself after episodic catastrophes. </span></p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">Still, I&#8217;d resist the fatalism. As I often say, you mitigate existential risk the same way you mitigate any other risk: by being more careful. I said it here, for example:</p><div class=\"digestPostEmbed-flwiST custom-css-email-digest-post-embed\" data-component-name=\"DigestPostEmbedStatic\" style=\"margin-bottom: 20px;padding: 0;position: relative;font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"auto\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"https://substack.com/redirect/7a6bb874-2d78-442f-82f8-f67a453d5c57?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8\" style=\"text-decoration: none;\"><h2 class=\"pencraft pc-reset color-pub-primary-text-NyXPlw line-height-36-XIK16z font-display-nhmvtD size-30-tZAWf_ weight-bold-DmI9lw reset-IxiVJZ\" style=\"list-style: none;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;-moz-osx-font-smoothing: antialiased;-webkit-appearance: optimizelegibility;-moz-appearance: optimizelegibility;appearance: optimizelegibility;font-family: 'SF Pro Display',-apple-system-headline,system-ui,-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif,'Apple Color Emoji','Segoe UI Emoji','Segoe UI Symbol';font-weight: 700;margin: 0;color: #363737;line-height: 36px;font-size: 30px;text-decoration: unset;\">The Apocalyptic Magisterium</h2></a></td></tr><tr><td><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"auto\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"vertical-align:middle;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"auto\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"vertical-align:middle;\"><div class=\"pencraft pc-reset color-pub-secondary-text-hGQ02T line-height-20-t4M0El font-meta-MWBumP size-11-NuY2Zx weight-medium-fw81nC transform-uppercase-yKDgcq reset-IxiVJZ meta-EgzBVA\" style=\"list-style: none;font-size: 11px;line-height: 20px;text-decoration: unset;color: #777777;margin: 0;font-family: 'SF Compact',-apple-system,system-ui,-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif,'Apple Color Emoji','Segoe UI Emoji','Segoe UI Symbol';font-weight: 500;text-transform: uppercase;letter-spacing: .2px;\"><a class=\"inheritColor-WetTGJ\" href=\"https://substack.com/profile/2769871-claire-berlinski\" style=\"color: inherit;text-decoration: none;\">Claire Berlinski</a></div></td><td width=\"4\" style=\"min-width:4px;\"></td><td style=\"vertical-align:middle;\"><div class=\"pencraft pc-reset color-pub-secondary-text-hGQ02T reset-IxiVJZ\" style=\"list-style: none;font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;text-decoration: unset;color: #777777;margin: 0;\">&#183;</div></td></tr></tbody></table></td><td width=\"4\" style=\"min-width:4px;\"></td><td style=\"vertical-align:middle;\"><div class=\"pencraft pc-reset color-pub-secondary-text-hGQ02T line-height-20-t4M0El font-meta-MWBumP size-11-NuY2Zx weight-medium-fw81nC transform-uppercase-yKDgcq reset-IxiVJZ meta-EgzBVA\" style=\"list-style: none;font-size: 11px;line-height: 20px;text-decoration: unset;color: #777777;margin: 0;font-family: 'SF Compact',-apple-system,system-ui,-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif,'Apple Color Emoji','Segoe UI Emoji','Segoe UI Symbol';font-weight: 500;text-transform: uppercase;letter-spacing: .2px;\">June 16, 2021</div></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td><div class=\"pencraft pc-paddingTop-24 pc-reset\" style=\"text-decoration: unset;list-style: none;padding-top: 24px;font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;\"><a href=\"https://substack.com/redirect/7a6bb874-2d78-442f-82f8-f67a453d5c57?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8\" style=\"text-decoration: none;\"><picture><source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!syf0!,w_424,h_212,c_fill,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep,g_auto/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcf788363-882e-4156-b57d-77c3ac4af7cf_900x350.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!syf0!,w_848,h_424,c_fill,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep,g_auto/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcf788363-882e-4156-b57d-77c3ac4af7cf_900x350.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!syf0!,w_1272,h_636,c_fill,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep,g_auto/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcf788363-882e-4156-b57d-77c3ac4af7cf_900x350.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!syf0!,w_1300,h_650,c_fill,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep,g_auto/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcf788363-882e-4156-b57d-77c3ac4af7cf_900x350.jpeg 1300w\" sizes=\"100vw\"><img class=\"img-OACg1c fullWidth-Ta6aEE pencraft pc-reset\" src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!syf0!,w_1300,h_650,c_fill,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep,g_auto/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcf788363-882e-4156-b57d-77c3ac4af7cf_900x350.jpeg\" sizes=\"100vw\" alt=\"The Apocalyptic Magisterium\" srcset=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!syf0!,w_424,h_212,c_fill,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep,g_auto/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcf788363-882e-4156-b57d-77c3ac4af7cf_900x350.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!syf0!,w_848,h_424,c_fill,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep,g_auto/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcf788363-882e-4156-b57d-77c3ac4af7cf_900x350.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!syf0!,w_1272,h_636,c_fill,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep,g_auto/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcf788363-882e-4156-b57d-77c3ac4af7cf_900x350.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!syf0!,w_1300,h_650,c_fill,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep,g_auto/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcf788363-882e-4156-b57d-77c3ac4af7cf_900x350.jpeg 1300w\" width=\"1300\" height=\"650\" style=\"text-decoration: unset;list-style: none;border: none !important;vertical-align: middle;display: block;-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic;max-width: 100%;height: auto;margin: 0 auto;object-fit: cover;width: 100%;max-height: 325px!important;\"></picture></a></div></td></tr><tr><td><a href=\"https://substack.com/redirect/7a6bb874-2d78-442f-82f8-f67a453d5c57?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8\" style=\"text-decoration: none;\"><p class=\"pencraft pc-reset\" style=\"text-decoration: unset;list-style: none;margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\"></p><p class=\"caption-QiPycG\" style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">When we think about catastrophic risks, we are prone to grave cognitive mishaps.<br></p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\"></p></a></td></tr><tr><td><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"auto\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" style=\"padding-top:0px;padding-bottom:0px;\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"vertical-align:middle;\"><a class=\"pencraft pc-reset align-center-y7ZD4w line-height-20-t4M0El font-text-qe4AeH size-13-hZTUKr weight-medium-fw81nC reset-IxiVJZ\" href=\"https://substack.com/redirect/7a6bb874-2d78-442f-82f8-f67a453d5c57?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8\" style=\"list-style: none;color: unset;text-align: center;text-decoration: unset;margin: 0;font-size: 13px;line-height: 20px;font-family: system-ui,-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif,'Apple Color Emoji','Segoe UI Emoji','Segoe UI Symbol';font-weight: 500;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"auto\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"vertical-align:middle;\"><span class=\"pencraft pc-reset color-accent-BVX_7M line-height-20-t4M0El font-text-qe4AeH size-14-MLPa7j weight-regular-mUq6Gb reset-IxiVJZ link-HREYZo\" style=\"list-style: none;text-decoration: unset;color: rgb(255,103,25);margin: 0;font-size: 14px;line-height: 20px;font-family: system-ui,-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif,'Apple Color Emoji','Segoe UI Emoji','Segoe UI Symbol';font-weight: 400;\">Read full story</span></td></tr></tbody></table></a></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></div><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">Our species has built restraints before: law, taboos, arms control, constitutionalism, scientific norms, insurance, central banks, public health, aviation safety, nuclear command protocols. We can do it. But can we build new institutions fast enough to keep cumulative technology from turning recurrent human stupidity into terminal human stupidity? That&#8217;s the question. </p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">The phrase &#8220;biological evolution&#8221; is, I think, doing too much work in your formulation. Evolution isn&#8217;t a command to &#8220;compete till death.&#8221; It also produces cooperation, kinship, reciprocity, symbiosis, restraint, and social intelligence. The problem isn&#8217;t evolution as such. The problem is that human beings evolved under conditions radically unlike those created by modern technology, and we&#8217;re not well-made for a world bursting with nuclear weapons, viral engineering, algorithmic propaganda, and artificial superintelligence. We have Stone Age threat responses and tribal cognition. Now, we have godlike instruments. A regrettable product launch.</p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">The alternatives aren&#8217;t necessarily &#8220;Eden or glass.&#8221; Eden isn&#8217;t coming back. Annihilation isn&#8217;t inevitable. There&#8217;s a plausible future somewhere between paradise and vitrification: a long, dangerous struggle to domesticate our own capabilities. If we succeed in building sufficiently robust institutions, perhaps we can keep our ancient primate impulses from using modern tools to turn the planet into a memorial to our cleverness. </p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">We should certainly try.</p><div style=\"font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;\"><hr style=\"margin: 32px 0;padding: 0;height: 1px;background: rgb(0,0,0,.1);border: none;\"></div><h3 class=\"header-anchor-post\" style=\"position: relative;font-family: 'SF Pro Display',-apple-system-headline,system-ui,-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif,'Apple Color Emoji','Segoe UI Emoji','Segoe UI Symbol';font-weight: bold;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;-moz-osx-font-smoothing: antialiased;-webkit-appearance: optimizelegibility;-moz-appearance: optimizelegibility;appearance: optimizelegibility;margin: 1em 0 0.625em 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 1.16em;font-size: 1.375em;text-align: center\"><strong>&#9739;&#9884;&#65039;&#127759;&#9884;&#65039;&#9739;&#9884;&#65039;&#127757;&#9884;&#65039;&#9739;&#9884;&#65039;&#127758;&#9884;&#65039;&#9739;</strong></h3><div style=\"font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;\"><hr style=\"margin: 32px 0;padding: 0;height: 1px;background: rgb(0,0,0,.1);border: none;\"></div><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\"><em>The questions below are related&#8212;or at least, I relate them in my reply&#8212;so I&#8217;ve answered them separately. I&#8217;ll send that answer tomorrow. </em></p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\"></p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\"><strong>QUESTION: I&#8217;m gonna ask you the hardest question possible right now. I&#8217;m an Iranian (expat) and I worry about Iran&#8217;s future tremendously. How do you see this current crisis playing out for the Iranian people? Are there any hopes for a free Iran that is also not completely destroyed?</strong></p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;text-align: right\"><em><strong>&#8212;Alireza</strong></em></p><div style=\"font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;\"><hr style=\"margin: 32px 0;padding: 0;height: 1px;background: rgb(0,0,0,.1);border: none;\"></div><h3 class=\"header-anchor-post\" style=\"position: relative;font-family: 'SF Pro Display',-apple-system-headline,system-ui,-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif,'Apple Color Emoji','Segoe UI Emoji','Segoe UI Symbol';font-weight: bold;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;-moz-osx-font-smoothing: antialiased;-webkit-appearance: optimizelegibility;-moz-appearance: optimizelegibility;appearance: optimizelegibility;margin: 1em 0 0.625em 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 1.16em;font-size: 1.375em;text-align: center\"><strong>&#9739;&#9884;&#65039;&#127759;&#9884;&#65039;&#9739;&#9884;&#65039;&#127757;&#9884;&#65039;&#9739;&#9884;&#65039;&#127758;&#9884;&#65039;&#9739;</strong></h3><div style=\"font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;\"><hr style=\"margin: 32px 0;padding: 0;height: 1px;background: rgb(0,0,0,.1);border: none;\"></div><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\"></p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\"><strong>QUESTION: How can society best deal with the crisis of antisemitism? Is this the new reality? How much worse can it get?</strong></p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\"><strong>Separately, as a parent of three children, how can one best prepare them for media literacy/misinformation?</strong></p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;text-align: right\"><em><strong><span>&#8212;</span><a href=\"https://substack.com/profile/843098-huxbnw?utm_source=substack-feed-item\" style=\"color: #e11d48;text-decoration: none;\">Huxbnw</a></strong></em></p><div style=\"font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;\"><hr style=\"margin: 32px 0;padding: 0;height: 1px;background: rgb(0,0,0,.1);border: none;\"></div><h3 class=\"header-anchor-post\" style=\"position: relative;font-family: 'SF Pro Display',-apple-system-headline,system-ui,-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif,'Apple Color Emoji','Segoe UI Emoji','Segoe UI Symbol';font-weight: bold;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;-moz-osx-font-smoothing: antialiased;-webkit-appearance: optimizelegibility;-moz-appearance: optimizelegibility;appearance: optimizelegibility;margin: 1em 0 0.625em 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 1.16em;font-size: 1.375em;text-align: center\"><strong>&#9739;&#9884;&#65039;&#127759;&#9884;&#65039;&#9739;&#9884;&#65039;&#127757;&#9884;&#65039;&#9739;&#9884;&#65039;&#127758;&#9884;&#65039;&#9739;</strong></h3><div style=\"font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;\"><hr style=\"margin: 32px 0;padding: 0;height: 1px;background: rgb(0,0,0,.1);border: none;\"></div><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\"><br><strong><span>QUESTION: So many points that I&#8217;ve considered and hoped that you, in one way or another, might address. Context: </span><a href=\"https://substack.com/redirect/60d5eab0-61af-4adf-8d0c-2dca142499d6?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8\" style=\"color: #e11d48;text-decoration: none;\">This article by Rich Lowry:</a></strong></p><blockquote style=\"border-left: 4px solid #e11d48;margin: 20px 0;padding: 0;\"><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\"><strong>We are witnessing the rise of the Dearborn Democrats, not in the literal sense, but in the same sense that Jeanne Kirkpatrick coined the phrase &#8220;San Francisco Democrats&#8221; in the 1980s. Back then, San Francisco, an elite coastal city, stood for the dovishness and permissiveness of liberalism; today, Dearborn, home to a large Arab-American enclave, stands for an all-consuming opposition to Israel with all that that entails, including a conspiratorial view of AIPAC and an underlying anti-Westernism.</strong></p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\"><strong>The ethos of the 2024 &#8220;uncommitted movement&#8221; in Michigan, urging voters not to vote for Joe Biden in protest of his support for the Gaza war, has now surged to a formidable position within the Democratic Party. A new Decision Desk poll shows that 75 percent of Democrats favor the Palestinians over the Israelis. The swing against Israel is even more pronounced among young voters. An Echelon Insights survey found that among Democrats under age 50, 54 percent had an unfavorable view of Iran, while 62 percent had an unfavorable view of Israel. </strong></p></blockquote><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\"><strong>Concerns on your end, Claire? Thank you.</strong></p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;text-align: right\"><em><strong><span>&#8212;</span><a href=\"https://substack.com/profile/6268785-russell-dad-whiting?utm_source=substack-feed-item\" style=\"color: #e11d48;text-decoration: none;\">Russell-Dad Whiting</a></strong></em></p><div style=\"font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;\"><hr style=\"margin: 32px 0;padding: 0;height: 1px;background: rgb(0,0,0,.1);border: none;\"></div><h3 class=\"header-anchor-post\" style=\"position: relative;font-family: 'SF Pro Display',-apple-system-headline,system-ui,-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif,'Apple Color Emoji','Segoe UI Emoji','Segoe UI Symbol';font-weight: bold;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;-moz-osx-font-smoothing: antialiased;-webkit-appearance: optimizelegibility;-moz-appearance: optimizelegibility;appearance: optimizelegibility;margin: 1em 0 0.625em 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 1.16em;font-size: 1.375em;text-align: center\"><strong>&#9739;&#9884;&#65039;&#127759;&#9884;&#65039;&#9739;&#9884;&#65039;&#127757;&#9884;&#65039;&#9739;&#9884;&#65039;&#127758;&#9884;&#65039;&#9739;</strong></h3><div style=\"font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;\"><hr style=\"margin: 32px 0;padding: 0;height: 1px;background: rgb(0,0,0,.1);border: none;\"></div><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\"><strong>QUESTION: Some background: if anyone asks me what I think about Israel/Palestine, I quote Isaac Deutscher: After WWII the Jews of Europe jumped out of a burning building and landed on the Palestinians. So my question now is: what about the settlers in the West Bank? (As for how Israel is waging war in Gaza and Lebanon, I don&#8217;t know what to believe re purported atrocities, although given it&#8217;s Netanyahu running things, I wouldn&#8217;t rule them out categorically.)</strong></p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;text-align: right\"><em><strong>&#8212;Doug1943</strong></em></p><div style=\"font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;\"><hr style=\"margin: 32px 0;padding: 0;height: 1px;background: rgb(0,0,0,.1);border: none;\"></div><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">Phew. </p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">Any further questions? </p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">&#8212;C.</p><div class=\"footnote\" data-component-name=\"FootnoteToDOMStatic\" style=\"line-height: 26px;display: flex;border-top: solid 1px rgb(0,0,0,.1);padding-top: 1.5em;font-size: 90%;flex-direction: row;align-items: baseline;\"><span class=\"footnote-number\" style=\"display: block;margin-right: 6px;min-width: 24px;\">1</span><div class=\"footnote-content\" style=\"font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;display: block;\"><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\">Many historians have written about the interaction of evangelical Protestantism, democratization, market society, print culture, westward movement, and reform zeal in this period&#8212;I can send you a bibliography if you want to read more about it. </p></div></div><div class=\"footnote\" data-component-name=\"FootnoteToDOMStatic\" style=\"line-height: 26px;display: flex;font-size: 90%;flex-direction: row;align-items: baseline;border-top: none;padding-top: 0;\"><span class=\"footnote-number\" style=\"display: block;margin-right: 6px;min-width: 24px;\">2</span><div class=\"footnote-content\" style=\"font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;display: block;\"><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\">If you attended the cognitive warfare symposium with Ren&#233;e di Resta, you know how this maneuver works. (And yes, that video is coming. Hold on. I&#8217;m using it in a little experimental project; I&#8217;ll show you soon.)</p></div></div><div class=\"footnote\" data-component-name=\"FootnoteToDOMStatic\" style=\"line-height: 26px;display: flex;font-size: 90%;flex-direction: row;align-items: baseline;border-top: none;padding-top: 0;\"><span class=\"footnote-number\" style=\"display: block;margin-right: 6px;min-width: 24px;\">3</span><div class=\"footnote-content\" style=\"font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;display: block;\"><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\">I asked Paul for clarification. He asked ChatGPT for help. This was ChatGPT&#8217;s reply:</p><blockquote style=\"border-left: 4px solid #e11d48;margin: 20px 0;padding: 0;\"><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\">This is a serious question&#8212;and it&#8217;s worth answering in a way that is concrete, credible, and grounded rather than speculative. There are areas where data can be delayed, revised, narrowed in scope, or shaped by political pressure, but it&#8217;s important to distinguish between routine statistical limitations and genuinely concerning opacity.</p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\">Here are several categories&#8212;with specific, defensible examples&#8212;that someone like Claire Berlinski would likely find substantive:</p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\"><strong>1) Public Health Data Gaps and Delays</strong></p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\">Worrisome pattern: narrowing of datasets, delayed releases, or changes in reporting standards.</p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\">During the Covid19 pandemic, the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention was criticized for:</p><ul style=\"margin-left: 20px;margin-top: 0;padding: 0;\"><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;mso-special-format: bullet;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;margin: 0;\">Delayed release of detailed hospitalization and breakthrough infection data.</p></li><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;mso-special-format: bullet;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;margin: 0;\">Withholding granular datasets (e.g., age-stratified booster effectiveness early on).</p></li></ul><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\">Outside Covid:</p><ul style=\"margin-left: 20px;margin-top: 0;padding: 0;\"><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;mso-special-format: bullet;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;margin: 0;\">Maternal mortality data in the US has faced methodology changes and pauses, making trend interpretation difficult.</p></li><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;mso-special-format: bullet;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;margin: 0;\">Drug overdose data (especially involving fentanyl analogs) is often lagged by many months, reducing real-time policy usefulness.</p></li></ul><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\">&#128073; Concern: Not necessarily malicious suppression, but policy-relevant data arriving too late or in altered form, which affects public understanding and response.</p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\"><strong>2) Military Casualty, Contractor, and Operational Data</strong></p><ul style=\"margin-left: 20px;margin-top: 0;padding: 0;\"><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;mso-special-format: bullet;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;margin: 0;\">Worrisome pattern: structural undercounting or classification.</p></li><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;mso-special-format: bullet;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;margin: 0;\">In conflicts like the War in Afghanistan and Iraq War:</p></li><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;mso-special-format: bullet;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;margin: 0;\">Official casualty figures often excluded contractors, who at times made up a large share of personnel.</p></li><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;mso-special-format: bullet;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;margin: 0;\">Data on civilian casualties was inconsistent and sometimes disputed by independent groups.</p></li></ul><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\">Ongoing:</p><ul style=\"margin-left: 20px;margin-top: 0;padding: 0;\"><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;mso-special-format: bullet;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;margin: 0;\">Drone strike data and targeting assessments have periodically been classified or discontinued (e.g., reduced transparency after earlier reporting initiatives).</p></li></ul><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\">&#128073; Concern: The public may get a systematically incomplete picture of human cost.</p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\"><strong>3) Surveillance and Intelligence Activity Transparency</strong></p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\">Worrisome pattern: discontinued or narrowed reporting after controversy.After the Edward Snowden disclosures:</p><ul style=\"margin-left: 20px;margin-top: 0;padding: 0;\"><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;mso-special-format: bullet;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;margin: 0;\">Some transparency reports (e.g., estimates of Americans affected by surveillance under certain authorities) became less detailed or ceased altogether.</p></li><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;mso-special-format: bullet;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;margin: 0;\">Reporting on programs under authorities like Section 702 of Foreign Intelligence Surveillance Act:</p></li><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;mso-special-format: bullet;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;margin: 0;\">Public disclosures exist but are often aggregated, partial, or redacted.</p></li></ul><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\">&#128073; Concern: Oversight exists, but public visibility into scope and impact is limited.</p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\"><strong>4) Economic Data Revisions and Measurement Blind Spots</strong></p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\">Worrisome pattern: technically valid methods that may obscure lived reality.</p><ul style=\"margin-left: 20px;margin-top: 0;padding: 0;\"><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;mso-special-format: bullet;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;margin: 0;\">Data from the Bureau of Labor Statistics:</p></li><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;mso-special-format: bullet;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;margin: 0;\">Inflation (CPI) excludes certain asset prices (like housing asset appreciation), which can diverge from perceived cost-of-living pressures.</p></li><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;mso-special-format: bullet;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;margin: 0;\">Employment figures are frequently revised significantly after initial release.</p></li><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;mso-special-format: bullet;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;margin: 0;\">Wealth inequality data:</p></li><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;mso-special-format: bullet;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;margin: 0;\">Heavily dependent on models and tax data, which can lag and underrepresent certain asset classes or offshore wealth.</p></li></ul><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\">&#128073; Concern: Not suppression, but methodological choices that shape narratives, sometimes unintentionally.</p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\"><strong>5) Environmental and Climate Monitoring Adjustments</strong></p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\">Worrisome pattern: changes in data availability or political interference concerns.</p><ul style=\"margin-left: 20px;margin-top: 0;padding: 0;\"><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;mso-special-format: bullet;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;margin: 0;\">During parts of the Trump administration environmental policy changes:</p></li><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;mso-special-format: bullet;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;margin: 0;\">Some environmental datasets were reportedly removed, relocated, or made harder to access (later restored in many cases).</p></li></ul><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\">Ongoing:</p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\">Air quality and pollution monitoring networks can have coverage gaps, especially in disadvantaged communities.</p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\">&#128073; Concern: Continuity and accessibility of long-term datasets can be vulnerable to political shifts.</p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\"><strong>6) Criminal Justice and Policing Data</strong></p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\">Worrisome pattern: incomplete national coverage.</p><ul style=\"margin-left: 20px;margin-top: 0;padding: 0;\"><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;mso-special-format: bullet;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;margin: 0;\">The Federal Bureau of Investigation crime database transition (to NIBRS):</p></li><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;mso-special-format: bullet;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;margin: 0;\">Resulted in temporary underreporting, as not all jurisdictions transitioned at once.</p></li><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;mso-special-format: bullet;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;margin: 0;\">Police use-of-force data:</p></li><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;mso-special-format: bullet;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;margin: 0;\">Still not comprehensively or uniformly reported nationwide.</p></li></ul><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\">&#128073; Concern: Major policy debates rely on fragmentary data.</p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\"><strong>7) Immigration and Border Enforcement Metrics.</strong><span> </span></p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\">Worrisome pattern: definitional shifts affecting interpretation.</p><ul style=\"margin-left: 20px;margin-top: 0;padding: 0;\"><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;mso-special-format: bullet;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;margin: 0;\">Data from U.S. Customs and Border Protection:</p></li><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;mso-special-format: bullet;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;margin: 0;\">&#8220;Encounters&#8221; vs. &#8220;unique individuals&#8221; can inflate or distort perceived trends due to repeat crossings.</p></li><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;mso-special-format: bullet;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;margin: 0;\">Asylum and detention statistics:</p></li><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;mso-special-format: bullet;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;margin: 0;\">Often reported in ways that require expert interpretation to avoid misleading conclusions.</p></li></ul><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\">&#128073; Concern: Numbers are real, but framing can mislead non-specialists.</p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\"><strong>Bottom Line (What&#8217;s Actually &#8220;Worrisome&#8221;).</strong></p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\">The most credible concern is not outright suppression in a conspiratorial sense, but:</p><ul style=\"margin-left: 20px;margin-top: 0;padding: 0;\"><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;mso-special-format: bullet;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;margin: 0;\">Selective discontinuation (certain reports no longer published)</p></li><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;mso-special-format: bullet;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;margin: 0;\">Aggregation that obscures detail</p></li><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;mso-special-format: bullet;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;margin: 0;\">Delays that reduce usefulness</p></li><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;mso-special-format: bullet;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;margin: 0;\">Methodological shifts that alter trend interpretation</p></li><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;mso-special-format: bullet;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;margin: 0;\">If you want a sharp formulation to give Ms. Berlinski:</p></li></ul><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\">&#8220;The risk isn&#8217;t that the US government fabricates data wholesale&#8212;it&#8217;s that it sometimes narrows, delays, or aggregates it in ways that make independent verification and timely public understanding much harder.&#8221;</p></blockquote></div></div><div class=\"footnote\" data-component-name=\"FootnoteToDOMStatic\" style=\"line-height: 26px;di