ight: 28px;margin: 0 12px 0 0;width: 28px;border-radius: 8px;\"><span class=\"embedded-post-publication-name\" style=\"font-family: 'SF Pro Display',-apple-system-headline,system-ui,-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif,'Apple Color Emoji','Segoe UI Emoji','Segoe UI Symbol';font-weight: 500;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;-moz-osx-font-smoothing: antialiased;-webkit-appearance: optimizelegibility;-moz-appearance: optimizelegibility;appearance: optimizelegibility;font-size: 16px;line-height: 28px;\">Doom Debates</span></div><div class=\"embedded-post-title-wrapper\" style=\"font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 8px;display: flex;align-items: flex-start;\"><img class=\"embedded-post-title-icon embedded-post-title-icon-static\" src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!XmrV!,w_19,c_limit,f_png,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fimg%2Fpodcast-headphones.svg\" style=\"border: none !important;vertical-align: middle;-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic;max-width: 100%;display: flex;height: 16px;margin: unset;stroke: #363737;margin-right: 9px;width: 16px;margin-top: 5px;\"><a class=\"embedded-post-title\" href=\"https://substack.com/redirect/1512f603-009f-4377-9520-158b239895b0?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8\" style=\"font-family: 'SF Pro Display',-apple-system-headline,system-ui,-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif,'Apple Color Emoji','Segoe UI Emoji','Segoe UI Symbol';font-weight: 700;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;-moz-osx-font-smoothing: antialiased;-webkit-appearance: optimizelegibility;-moz-appearance: optimizelegibility;appearance: optimizelegibility;color: #363737;font-size: 18px;text-decoration: none;\">Talking AI Doom with Dr. Claire Berlinski &amp; Friends</a></div><div class=\"embedded-post-body\" style=\"font-family: system-ui,-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif,'Apple Color Emoji','Segoe UI Emoji','Segoe UI Symbol';font-size: 16px;line-height: 1.6;margin-bottom: 16px;color: #777777;margin-top: 4px;\">Dr. Claire Berlinski is a journalist, Oxford PhD, and author of The Cosmopolitan Globalist. She invited me to her weekly symposium to make the case for AI as an existential risk, and discuss how informed people can help&#8230;</div><div class=\"embedded-post-cta-wrapper\" style=\"display: inline-flex;box-sizing: border-box;border-radius: 8px;border: 1px solid rgb(0,0,0,.1);padding: 10px 12px;font-size: 16px;line-height: 16px;margin-bottom: 16px;font-weight: 500;align-items: center;\"><img class=\"embedded-post-cta-icon-static\" width=\"12\" height=\"12\" src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!fO23!,w_12,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fimg%2Faudio-player-play.png\" style=\"border: none !important;vertical-align: middle;display: block;-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic;max-width: 100%;height: auto;margin: 0 auto;margin-right: 9px;\"><a class=\"embedded-post-cta\" href=\"https://substack.com/redirect/1512f603-009f-4377-9520-158b239895b0?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8\" style=\"color: #363737;text-decoration: none;\">Listen now</a></div><div class=\"embedded-post-meta\" style=\"line-height: 26px;color: #777777;font-size: 14px;\">a month ago &#183; 10 likes &#183; 1 comment &#183; Liron Shapira</div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"footnote\" data-component-name=\"FootnoteToDOMStatic\" style=\"line-height: 26px;display: flex;font-size: 90%;flex-direction: row;align-items: baseline;border-top: none;padding-top: 0;\"><span class=\"footnote-number\" style=\"display: block;margin-right: 6px;min-width: 24px;\">5</span><div class=\"footnote-content\" style=\"font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;display: block;\"><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\">Something struck me as I looked at those articles again, which is that much of the world now understands the points I made. They didn&#8217;t, when I first made them. I wrote those essays in 2016; I rewrote and republished them in 2022, but my changes were stylistic, not substantive. They were all meant to be chapters in a book, one that I never published. (I published them here, obviously. I&#8217;m glad I did; I&#8217;m sure they were more widely read than they would have been had I put them in a book, because no one reads books anymore.) </p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\"><span>When I wrote them, very few people, and certainly very few Americans, grasped that Trump was not </span><em>sui generis</em><span>; he was not unprecedented; and he was not unpredictable.</span><em> </em><span>He was the embodiment of a distinct political phenomenon&#8212;a global trend that had been underway for more than a decade. Most Americans didn&#8217;t realize this, which is why I wrote that book. I realized this not because I&#8217;m uncannily prescient, but because I&#8217;d already lived through it, in Turkey. I recognized the style instantly. </span></p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\">If you read those articles now, you&#8217;ll think they tell you nothing you don&#8217;t know already. But I wrote them&#8212;including the article about the rules for destroying a liberal democracy&#8212;before Trump&#8217;s first term in office. I can guarantee you that very few people knew any of that in 2015. Every editor who looked at the manuscript passed. I can no longer recall what they said, exactly, but I know they didn&#8217;t find the case compelling. </p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\">So we&#8217;ve made some progress: There&#8217;s a larger awareness of the problem, which is a necessary first step.</p></div></div><div class=\"footnote\" data-component-name=\"FootnoteToDOMStatic\" style=\"line-height: 26px;display: flex;font-size: 90%;flex-direction: row;align-items: baseline;border-top: none;padding-top: 0;\"><span class=\"footnote-number\" style=\"display: block;margin-right: 6px;min-width: 24px;\">6</span><div class=\"footnote-content\" style=\"font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;display: block;\"><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\"><span> The US rate is 5.8, just shy of the global average: 7.6. France: 1.3. Haiti: 41. Japan: 0.2. South Africa: 43.7. The highest rate in of homicide in the world? Turks and Caicos, at 76.3. (Isn&#8217;t Turks and Caicos supposed to be a pleasant Caribbean vacation spot? What&#8217;s going on over there? That&#8217;s </span><em>far</em><span> higher than any other country. Could the figure be some kind of weird statistical artifact?) All of these numbers are from the United Nations Office on Drugs and Crime, via </span><strong><a href=\"https://substack.com/redirect/925e6ac6-7ebd-4939-8a82-747ca89f4b31?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8\" style=\"color: #e11d48;text-decoration: none;\">Wikipedia</a></strong><span>. </span></p><div class=\"captioned-image-container-static\" style=\"font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;margin: 32px auto;margin-bottom: 0;\"><figure style=\"width: 100%;margin: 0 auto;\"><table class=\"image-wrapper\" width=\"100%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOMStatic\" style=\"mso-padding-alt: 1em 0 1.6em;\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"text-align: center;\"></td><td class=\"content\" align=\"left\" width=\"724\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><a class=\"image-link\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substack.com/redirect/4a7d804c-bdf7-45f1-b568-aca954133a8f?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8\" style=\"position: relative;flex-direction: column;align-items: center;padding: 0;width: auto;height: auto;border: none;text-decoration: none;display: block;margin: 0;\"><img class=\"wide-image\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/3544c097-da90-4858-8130-763fffa700c5_474x316.webp&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:316,&quot;width&quot;:474,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:724,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;Best Beaches in the Turks and Caicos Islands&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Best Beaches in the Turks and Caicos Islands&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" alt=\"Best Beaches in the Turks and Caicos Islands\" title=\"Best Beaches in the Turks and Caicos Islands\" width=\"550\" height=\"366.6666666666667\" src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!-7Fi!,w_1100,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3544c097-da90-4858-8130-763fffa700c5_474x316.webp\" style=\"border: none !important;vertical-align: middle;display: block;-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic;height: auto;margin-bottom: 0;width: auto !important;max-width: 100% !important;margin: 0 auto;\"></a></td><td style=\"text-align: center;\"></td></tr></tbody></table><figcaption class=\"image-caption\" style=\"box-sizing: content-box;color: rgb(119,119,119);font-size: 14px;line-height: 20px;font-weight: 400;letter-spacing: -.15px;margin-top: 8px;width: 70%;padding-left: 15%;padding-right: 15%;text-align: center;margin-bottom: 0;padding-bottom: 0;\">Turks and Caicos: Not as nice as it looks.</figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class=\"footnote\" data-component-name=\"FootnoteToDOMStatic\" style=\"line-height: 26px;display: flex;font-size: 90%;flex-direction: row;align-items: baseline;margin-bottom: 0;border-top: none;padding-top: 0;\"><span class=\"footnote-number\" style=\"display: block;margin-right: 6px;min-width: 24px;\">7</span><div class=\"footnote-content\" style=\"font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;display: block;\"><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\"><span>By the way, Paul&#8217;s an </span><em>old</em><span> friend: We&#8217;ve known each other since I was twelve years old. He had a huge influence on me! May everyone be lucky enough to still be friends with someone they met when they were twelve. </span></p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;min-width: 10px;\"></p></div></div></div></div><div class=\"container-border\" style=\"margin: 32px 0 0;width: 100%;box-sizing: border-box;border-top: 1px solid #e6e6e6;font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;\"></div><div class=\"typography\" style=\"--image-offset-margin: -120px;font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;\"><div class=\"postscript\" style=\"margin: 32px 0;font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;\"><div class=\"body markup\" dir=\"auto\" style=\"text-align: initial;font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;width: 100%;word-break: break-word;margin-bottom: 16px;\"><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;margin-top: 0;\"><em>This post is for subscribers of </em><a href=\"https://substack.com/redirect/2/eyJlIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9jbGFpcmViZXJsaW5za2kuc3Vic3RhY2suY29tP3V0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1lbWFpbC1ob21lJnI9MWllZnkiLCJwIjoxOTU1MTI0MjAsInMiOjE2MjM1LCJmIjpmYWxzZSwidSI6MjUzODE0MiwiaWF0IjoxNzc3MjQwMTU3LCJleHAiOjIwOTI4MTYxNTcsImlzcyI6InB1Yi0wIiwic3ViIjoibGluay1yZWRpcmVjdCJ9.gpLQFkuIu8BWuEmPW1jmb1N9geYCaEeCSD7RaHqoiVQ?\" style=\"color: #e11d48;text-decoration: none;\">The Cosmopolitan Globalist</a><em>, but we have no objection if you&#8217;d like to share it with friends, in fact, we encourage it.</em></p><p class=\"button-wrapper\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;url&quo